    "question_id" : 79563772,
    "body" : "<p>You can do this by changing your <code>@Named</code> method expecting the entire input source.</p>\n<pre><code>@Mapper\npublic interface TargetMapper {\n\n  TargetMapper INSTANCE = Mappers.getMapper(TargetMapper.class);\n\n  @Mapping(target = &quot;sum&quot;, source = &quot;.&quot;, qualifiedByName = &quot;sumThree&quot;)\n  Target mapMe(Source src);\n\n  @Named(&quot;sumThree&quot;)\n  default int sum(Source src) {\n    return src.a() + src.b() + src.c();\n  }\n  \n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>in the <code>@Mapping</code> annotation are yor providing the entire source element by <code>.</code><br />\nThus, you can access it by referenced <code>sumThree</code> method to perform the calculation.</p>\n",
